{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Prohibit schools from having CCTV in toilets or changing rooms",
        "additional_details": "Some schools have installed CCTV in bathroom areas to stop bullying and vandalism, but what about the right to go to the bathroom in private?\r\n \r\nAllowing CCTV to be installed in school bathrooms and changing rooms could intrude on the privacy of students.\r\n \r\nWe teach children about private areas and spaces from a young age and this should be reflected in protections for private spaces.\r\n \r\nWe believe the ability of schools to place CCTV in private areas creates serious safeguarding issues.",
        "background": "The Government should ban schools from having CCTV in toilets or changing rooms, so no new cameras can be installed, and any existing cameras must be removed.",
